content_data.transcript:
Conditional statements let you make decisions in your code.

Basic if statement:
if age >= 18:
    print("You are an adult")

if-else:
if age >= 18:
    print("Adult")
else:
    print("Minor")

if-elif-else:
if score >= 90:
    grade = "A"
elif score >= 80:
    grade = "B"
elif score >= 70:
    grade = "C"
else:
    grade = "F"

Comparison operators: ==, !=, <, >, <=, >=
Logical operators: and, or, not
